      </slide>
      <slide>
        <title>Activity 5.1.1 (~5 min)</title>
        <p original-id="GT1-s3a2i1p1" internal-id="p-GT1-c-b-a-a">
The image in Figure 46  illustrates how the linear transformation
<m original-id="GT1-s3a2i1p1m2" internal-id="m-GT1-c-b-a-a-b">T : \IR^2 \rightarrow \IR^2</m> given by the
standard matrix <m original-id="GT1-s3a2i1p1m3" internal-id="m-GT1-c-b-a-a-c">A = \left[\begin{array}{cc} 2 &amp; 0 \\ 0 &amp; 3 \end{array}\right]</m>
