      <slide>
        <title>Fact 5.1.12 </title>
        <p original-id="GT1-s3f20s1p1" internal-id="p-GT1-c-t-a-a">
Since the transformation given by the standard matrix <m original-id="GT1-s3f20s1p1m1" internal-id="m-GT1-c-t-a-a-a">AB</m> is obtained
by applying the transformations given by <m original-id="GT1-s3f20s1p1m2" internal-id="m-GT1-c-t-a-a-b">A</m> and <m original-id="GT1-s3f20s1p1m3" internal-id="m-GT1-c-t-a-a-c">B</m>, it follows that
<me original-id="GT1-s3f20s1p1m4" internal-id="me-GT1-c-t-a-a-d">\det(AB)=\det(A)\det(B)=\det(B)\det(A)=\det(BA)</me>.
